<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="332" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1222,2102,611,722]" pageId="0" pageNumber="332">• Minuscule to small quadrupedal carnivores with short limbs, slender bodies, pointed rostra, and cuspidate teeth.</paragraph>
<caption box="[1220,1391,925,958]" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="332" startId="0.[1220,1233,925,958]" targetBox="[1377,1718,723,912]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1219,2101,925,1236]" box="[1220,1391,925,958]" pageId="0" pageNumber="332">• 5-30 cm.</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="332" startId="0.[1220,1233,970,999]" targetBox="[205,1153,610,1236]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1219,2101,925,1236]" pageId="0" pageNumber="332">• Holarctic, Indo-Malayan, Afrotropical, and Neotropical Regions.</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1219,2101,925,1236]" pageId="0" pageNumber="332">• Typically moist areas with dense ground cover, from sea level to elevations of about 4000 m.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1219,2101,925,1236]" box="[1220,1748,1119,1157]" pageId="0" pageNumber="332">• 25 genera, 448 species, 628 taxa.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1219,2101,925,1236]" pageId="0" pageNumber="332">• 11 species Critically Endangered, 34 species Endangered, 24 species Vulnerable; none Extinct since 1600.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
